Class ResizeableArrayBag<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ResizeableArrayBag<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BagInterface<T>

    public class ResizeableArrayBag<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements BagInterface<T>
    Implementation of BagInterface that uses an array internally to store data. Implements automatic array resizing.

    The size of the internal array is doubled every time an entry is added to the bag that causes the internal array to exceed its capacity.

      • union

        public BagInterface<T> union(BagInterface<T> otherBag)
        Description copied from interface: BagInterface
        Takes the union of this Bag and an input BagInterface.

        The result may contain duplicate items. For example, if this bag contains Strings "a", "b", "c", and the input bag contains "c", "d", "c", then the result will be a bag containing "a", "b", "c", "c", "d", "c" (note that as with all bag objects order is not guaranteed).

        This method does not affect the contents of either bag.

        Specified by:
        union in interface BagInterface<T>
        Parameters:
        otherBag - The second bag to be used in the union.
        Returns:
        A new BagInterface containing all of the elements of both bags.

      • difference

        public BagInterface<T> difference(BagInterface<T> otherBag)
        Description copied from interface: BagInterface
        Takes the difference of this Bag and an input BagInterface. The difference is calculated by looking for elements contained in this bag that the otherBag does not contain.

        The difference of two bags may contain duplicate items. For example, if this bag contains Strings "a", "c", "c", "c" and the input bag contains "c", "d", then the result will be a bag containing "a", "c", "c" (note that as with all bag objects order is not guaranteed). In other words, the difference is not only dependent on which elements are present in each bag, but also the quantity that each is present.

        This method does not affect the contents of either bag.

        Specified by:
        difference in interface BagInterface<T>
        Parameters:
        otherBag - The bag whose elements are subtracted from this bag (ie the second bag in the subtraction operation).
        Returns:
        A new BagInterface containing all elements in this bag that the other bag does not contain.

      • intersection

        public BagInterface<T> intersection(BagInterface<T> otherBag)
        Description copied from interface: BagInterface
        Takes the intersection of this Bag and an input BagInterface. The intersection is elements that are present in both bags.

        The intersection may contain duplicate items. For example, if this bag contains Strings "a", "c", "c", "d" and the input bag contains "c", "c", "d", the output bag will contain "c", "c", "d". (note that as with all bag objects order is not guaranteed). In other words, the difference is not only dependent on which elements are present in each bag, but also the quantity that each is present.

        This method does not affect the contents of either bag.

        Specified by:
        intersection in interface BagInterface<T>
        Parameters:
        otherBag - The second bag to be used in the intersection operation.
        Returns:
        A new BagInterface with the result of the intersection.
